## 2. The Big Picture — How Mike Thinks

Think of Mike as a **large law firm with specialized departments**. When a client walks in with a request:

1. **The receptionist** (Intent Classifier) listens to what the client wants and decides which department should handle it.
2. **The managing partner** (Task Planner) breaks the request into specific work items and assigns them to the right specialists.
3. **The specialists** (Agents) each do their piece of work — research, drafting, compliance review, document analysis — using their own tools and expertise.
4. **The quality partner** (Self-Critique Agent) reviews everything before it goes to the client.
5. **The senior partner** (Response Generator) combines all the work into one polished, professional deliverable.
6. **The ethics officer** (Output Validator) checks that nothing violates legal ethics rules before it leaves the firm.

The entire flow happens in real-time, streaming status updates to the user as each step completes.

